description: {"blocks":[{"key":"ar9u6","text":"Drosophila small RNA sequencing samples are often overwhelmed by the abundant 30-nucleotide 2S rRNA fragment. Small RNA of interest can be isolated from total RNA without this fragment using gel size separation and a block oligo with sequence complementarity to the 2S rRNA fragment. In this protocol we detail the equipment, reagents and method for recovering small RNA (size range ~17-29 nucleotides) from total RNA using a urea-PAGE gel and ethanol precipitation, in preparation for deep sequencing. We draw on previous publications and available protocols to present step-by-step instructions with tips and tricks for successful small RNA isolation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":0,"length":11}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"faemh","text":"Soak gel combs in 3% hydrogen peroxide for 15 minutes on each side.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e5jcg","text":"Rinse combs and spray with 70% ethanol.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dn5e7","text":"Spray everything else with RNase Away, rinse with DI water, and spray with 70% ethanol.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1qh5g","text":"Set all equipment to dry on the benchtop (spread with fresh benchtop paper) overnight.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"drn2b","text":"Note: It's best to begin in the late afternoon or evening so that the equipment isn't sitting out to dry when people are running around doing things in the lab.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":5}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5u18a","text":"Turn on heat block to 65 degrees C and start thawing (on ice) 10% APS, RNA sample buffer, ladder aliquots, and RNA samples.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"98dqe","text":"Make 1% agar solution for sealing the gel:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8klo6","text":"Add 4 g agar to 400 ml DI water.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ct94t","text":"Microwave, swirling occasionally, until agar has dissolved.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5pv80","text":"Let cool slightly, to around 70 degrees C, to avoid warping the bottom gel spacer.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"83git","text":"If you let it cool a bit too long, you can re-microwave it to re-dissolve the agar.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"magp","text":"Assemble the gel apparatus:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4vdid","text":"Set up the gel power supply.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2fjrm","text":"Assemble gel apparatus reservoirs, orienting the apparatus with the blue part of the bottom reservoir facing you. This orients the bottom reservoirs so they are facing to your right and left, and makes for for easy access to both sides for sample loading.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8spge","text":"Fill gel apparatus bottom with 0.5X TBE. ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8f36q","text":"Remove comb gently from gel.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1at8l","text":"Remove cassette from agar.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5ka30","text":"Remove binder clips and gel tape.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5jlm3","text":"Remove bottom spacer from cassette.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"en0g3","text":"Clean gel pieces from near comb and agar from near bottom.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3nurv","text":"Load cassettes (make sure no bubbles are introduced into the bottom gap by placing cassette in at a sliding angle) and clamp to gel rig. If bubbles are introduced, you can remove them using a bent syringe. ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8bdkq","text":"Make sure TBE in bottom reservoir is at least 5 mm above bottom edge of cassette.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"27koh","text":" Fill the top of the aparatus with 0.5X TBE, covering top edge of cassette by at least 5 mm.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ca0cc","text":"Pre-run at a constant current of 40 mA for 30 minutes. Gel temperature should reach ~30 degrees C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3rm2","text":"While gel is pre-running, prepare samples:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"78v5m","text":"Vortex and spin down samples and RNA ladder.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c2rff","text":"Mix 30 ul sample buffer with each 30 ul sample of total RNA (total sample loading volume = 60 ul per well).","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cpssp","text":"For each ladder well used, mix 10 ul sample buffer with 10 ul aliquote of ladder (total ladder loading volume = 20 ul per well). Pipette to mix.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a7ecc","text":"Heat samples and ladder at 65 C for 10 minutes.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bb6o","text":"Put on ice for 5 minutes. ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4uor2","text":"Vortex and spin down briefly.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"649lv","text":"Load samples:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8eu73","text":"Flush urea out of all wells thoroughly.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c3v4b","text":"Flush urea out of first well (second flush). Load ladder/sample. Repeat for each well in turn.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"56prf","text":"Run at a constant current of 30 mA for ~1 hour, until the lower bromophenol blue bands are near the middle of the gel.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8rpbo","text":"Once gel has finished running:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7vgh6","text":"For each gel, mix 30 ul SYBR Gold with ~300 ml 0.5X TBE in a plastic tray for staining. ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"96ea3","text":"Label trays if running more than one gel.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9p6gg","text":"Place one sheet protector in each tray.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9unmq","text":"Remove gels from cassettes for staining:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5jes1","text":"Stop gel power, remove top, and remove gel cassettes from apparatus.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"efavk","text":"To remove gel from cassette, pull out spacers (can use tweezers/forceps), pry plates apart, and loosen gel with fingers.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"59pme","text":"Be very careful not to tear the gel or to touch the lanes.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f9404","text":"Place quickly and gently on top of the sheet protector in plastic tub of stain.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8023q","text":"Stain gel(s) on a shaker at 115 RPM, covered, for 10-15 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e4m9p","text":"Visualize gels with a UV illuminator:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e7lnt","text":"Lift gel out of tub using the sheet protector, draining the buffer by tilting slightly.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9k6av","text":"Lay the gel, with sheet protector underneath, on the UV light box.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9eu21","text":"Manipulate to exclude air bubbles.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ehgqi","text":"Take a picture.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"245bb","text":"Excising the small RNA:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"822b8","text":"For each lane, cut bands carefully between the 2S rRNA band and the lowest band on the ladder, using a new glass cover slip for each sample. ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"92fi3","text":"Avoid collecting more gel than is absolutely necessary (excess gel will decrease total RNA yield). ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"597t2","text":"Cut up each slice into tiny pieces. ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"72mco","text":"Use the cover slip to scoop the pieces into 2 ml tubes.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ens40","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"evd7e","text":"Example gel photo: dotted line shows where to cut slice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ceqtt","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"11bd0","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"bdvrn","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"D7137F903DCE11ED9D68BD42AD473E8A","height":288,"id":304058,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"5ju13","text":"Example gel photo: dotted line shows where to cut slice.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mime":"image/png","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"example gel picture.png","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/ji76bxvy7.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/ji74bxvy7.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/ji75bxvy7.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/ji73bxvy7.webp","width":204}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6b967","text":"Add 1.2 ml of 0.3 NaCl to each tube. Make sure slices can slosh around in the tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9s203","text":"Rotate at room temperature overnight to elute small RNA from the gel slices.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8lsck","text":"Transfer gel elution to fresh 1.7 ml tubes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dq37i","text":"Spin at 17,000 G for 1 minute, to collect tiny gel bits at the bottom.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c1rkb","text":"Split each gel elution into 3 fresh tubes, 340 ul each. Some liquid will be left over; avoid taking the liquid at the bottom of spun tubes, as trying to get it results in gel fragments in your eluate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"dmjnr","text":"Add 1 ul (20 ug) glycogen to each tube. Vortex and spin briefly.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3308l","text":"Add 3 volumes of 100% ethanol. Vortex and spin briefly.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9jtlk","text":"Incubate on ice for 1 hour.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ce8v0","text":"Spin at 17,000 G at 4 degrees C for 15 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"38s1e","text":"Vortex for 10 seconds to strip precipitates from the wall.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"baorn","text":"Spin again at 17,000 G at 4 degrees C for 15 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cijcn","text":"Carefully remove supernatant without touching pellet. We used a 200 uL pipette.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5lfk8","text":"Add 900 ul of 75% ethanol, and vortex briefly.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"arjlp","text":"Spin at 17,000 G at 4 degrees C for 5 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"crmfe","text":"Carefully remove almost all supernatant without touching pellet. We used a 200 uL pipette set at 200 uL.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"dajk1","text":"Spin at 17,000 G at 4 degrees C for 1 minute.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5l171","text":"Carefully remove residual ethanol. We used a 20 uL pipette.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9k6l7","text":"Final volume of each sample will be 7 ul. Store at -80 degrees C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
